extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.function.Consumer<T>>, MakesCapturesOnFinishing<THIS>
    This class is designed to build actions to be performed on different objects. Also it may be used to build chains of same actions on different objects.

      • makeImageCaptureOnFinish

        public THIS makeImageCaptureOnFinish()
        Marks that it is needed to produce a BufferedImage after invocation of Consumer.accept(Object) on built resulted Consumer. This image is produced by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object)

        NOTE 1

        This image is produced if there is any subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor that may produce a BufferedImage.

        NOTE 2

        A subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor should be able to handle input values T on success/on failure.
